cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques, specifically recurrent neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves training and optimization of the model, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of neural networks for language modelling and author identification can also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which can be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of shared recurrent layers can be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
